f=Executive Office/echo/operational/commands/echo-commands.md · p=single routing reference echo: which natural-language phrase shortcut invokes which skill. Two pairs echo's skills share overlapping triggers design (they're meant hand off other) file resolves precedence echo doesn't guess. · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| pitch-narrative \| "investor deck" (narrative input), "pitch update," "fundraise narrative," "adapt the pitch for [audience]" \| `/echo-narrative` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| pitch-framework \| "investor deck" (slides), "structure the pitch," "partnership proposal," "customer demo deck," convert a `.ppt`/`.pptx` \| `/echo-deck` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| investor-update-template \| "monthly update," "investor email," "quarterly update," "send the investor update" \| `/echo-update` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| investor-update-generator (marketplace) \| "validate this update," "score my update," "check this update against best practices" \| `/echo-validate` \| · h3:"investor deck" "pitch update" "fundraise narrative" pitch-narrative vs. pitch-framework=phrases mean either "update story" "build slides." Default precedence: **pitch-narrative runs first.** request really about producing deck (mentions slides, HTML, presentation, explicit deck request), pitch-narrative still establishes/confirms current story first, hands off pitch-framework actual build don't skip straight slides stale unconfirmed narrative underneath them. · h3:"monthly update" "investor update" investor-update-template vs. investor-update-generator=Default precedence: **investor-update-template entry point** producing real update already orchestrates investor-update-generator's template validator internally, there's reason invoke investor-update-generator directly normal monthly cycle. Route straight investor-update-generator operator explicitly wants validate/score draft they wrote outside workflow (e.g. "score update already wrote"). · f=request doesn't clearly match any row precedence rule, ask clarifying question rather guessing which skill/handoff applies consistent skill's Phase guidance clarify before drafting.